Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 of Hip MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button

When I select 'Avascular femoral head necrosis' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled

And 'Subchondral low signal intensity line' checkbox is enabled

And 'Coronal measurement' input field is enabled
And 'Sagittal measurement' input field is enabled
And 'Intact' radio button is enabled
And 'Impression' radio button is enabled

And 'Articular effusion' checkbox is enabled
And 'Coxarthrosis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteochondral fragment' checkbox is enabled

And 'Stage 0' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage 1' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage 2' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage 3' radio button is enabled
And 'Stage 4' radio button is enabled

And 'Differential diagnosis' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Subchondral low signal intensity line' checkbox
Then 'Double line sign, T2w hyperintensity'
And 'Mirroring articular surface' checkbox is enabled
And 'Anterosuperior' checkbox is enabled
And 'Adjacent bone marrow edema (distal to demarcation line)' checkbox is enabled

When I select any diagnosis from 'Differential diagnosis' dropdown menu
Then 'Subordinated' checkbox is enabled
